Deep-Dive Analysis Report

1. Core KPIs Defined

Total Sales: ₹ 6,18,472.40

Total Orders: 4,922

Average Order Value (AOV): ₹ 930.03

Unique Customers: 665

2. Deep-Dive Methodology 

A Segmentation Analysis was conducted using the RFM (Recency, Frequency, Monetary) model:

Recency: Days since last purchase

Frequency: Number of orders per customer

Monetary: Total spending

Customers were scored (1–5) and segmented into behavioral groups:

Champions

Loyal Customers

Big Spenders

At Risk

Others

3. Key Insights (Based on  RFM ANALYSIS)
🟢 Champions (20 Customers)

Top-performing customers with high recency, frequency, and spending

Small but most valuable segment

👉 Strategy: Loyalty programs, VIP offers

🔵 Loyal Customers (246 Customers)

Largest valuable segment

Frequent and consistent buyers

👉 Strategy: Upselling, cross-selling, personalized recommendations

🟡 Big Spenders (106 Customers)

High spending but less frequent purchases

👉 Strategy: Encourage repeat purchases with targeted offers

🔴 At-Risk Customers (146 Customers)

Haven’t purchased recently

High chance of churn

👉 Strategy: Re-engagement campaigns, discounts

⚪ Others (147 Customers)

Moderate/low engagement customers

👉 Strategy: Improve engagement through marketing campaigns

4. Business Impact

-> Identified high-value customer segments (Champions & Loyal)

-> Detected 146 at-risk customers, enabling proactive retention strategies

-> Found that Loyal Customers (246) drive consistent revenue

-> Segmentation supports targeted marketing & personalization

5. Conclusion

The RFM-based segmentation effectively highlights customer behavior patterns, enabling the business to improve retention, maximize revenue, and design targeted marketing strategies.
